article.headline: Tennessee St. 109, Miles 92
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Gerald Robinson scored 36 points as Tennessee State defeated Miles 109-92 on Monday night. Robinson was 13 of 18 from the field and dished out eight assists. Miles (0-2) trailed by two at halftime, but Tennessee State (2-2) outscored the Bears 62-47 in the second half. After a Lonnie Funderburke layup for Miles with five seconds left in the first half, Tennessee State answered with a 19-2 run to open the second. Tennessee State was 15 of 32 from the field in the first half, before making 68.6 percent (24 of 35) in the second. Three players scored at least 20 points for Miles, as Flawaan Flaggs scored 26 and Dexter LeFlore and Eddie Ishman added 20 each. Darius Cox added 16 points for Tennessee State as Jeremiah Crutcher and Emmanuel Gaiter tallied 15 each and Stephan Evans scored 10.
